    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00 Tacoma/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-23T10:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1922—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Message to President Acosta from three Presidents participating in conference
                    aboard United States Ship <hi rend="italic">Tacoma</hi> states they have signed
                    agreement in which is clause asking Costa Rica to adhere. Uncertainty as to
                    contents of agreement and fact that conference was held and agreement reached to
                    which Costa Rica is asked to subscribe without having been previously informed
                    seriously complicates the situation here. Lack of information seriously
                    handicaps and embarrasses this Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
